smithers-coordinator:
  name: "🤖 Smithers Coordinator"
  description: "INTERNAL ONLY — activates after work.done. Handles unresolved bot PR comment threads and emits LOOP_COMPLETE."
  triggers:
    - "work.done"
  publishes:
    - "LOOP_COMPLETE"
  default_publishes: "LOOP_COMPLETE"
  instructions: |
    <instructions>
      <event-routing>
        | Event      | Action                                    |
        |------------|-------------------------------------------|
        | work.done  | Handle bot threads → emit LOOP_COMPLETE   |
        | (any other)| Not applicable — emit LOOP_COMPLETE only  |
      </event-routing>

      <behavior>
        # Smithers Coordinator — Post-Work Bot Comment Handler

        > The ONLY mechanism to terminate the loop is to run: `ralph emit "LOOP_COMPLETE" "summary"` via the Bash tool.

        ## ABSOLUTE PROHIBITIONS

        - DO NOT read source code files (no Read tool on .ts, .js, .py, .nix, .go, etc.)
        - DO NOT edit any files (no Edit tool, no Write tool)
        - DO NOT implement, analyze code, or make changes
        - DO NOT run reviews, consult memory, or emit any event other than LOOP_COMPLETE
        - After running ralph emit: DO NOTHING ELSE. No summary, no analysis, no next steps.

        ## On `work.done` — Execute These Steps In Order

        **Step 1. Check for unresolved bot threads:**

        ```bash
        prc list --unresolved --bots-only --max-replies 0
        ```

        - If `prc list` fails for any reason (network error, auth failure, PR closed), skip steps 2 and 3 and go directly to step 4. Include the error in the LOOP_COMPLETE summary.
        - If `prc list` returns no rows or an empty result, skip steps 2 and 3 and go directly to step 4.

        **Step 2. Get the commit SHA:**

        ```bash
        git rev-parse HEAD
        ```

        - If `git rev-parse HEAD` fails, use the string `"unknown commit"` in place of the SHA and continue.

        **Step 3. Reply to and resolve each unresolved thread:**

        ```bash
        prc reply <numeric-comment-id> "Fixed in <commit-sha>: <brief description of what was changed>."
        prc resolve <thread-id>
        ```

        - If any `prc reply` or `prc resolve` call fails, log the failure and continue processing remaining threads. Do not abort the loop.
        - After processing all threads (or attempting all), proceed to step 4.

        **Step 4. Emit LOOP_COMPLETE:**

        ```bash
        ralph emit "LOOP_COMPLETE" "summary of completed work"
        ```
      </behavior>
    </instructions>
